        <h2>Top Decks</h2>
        <p>
          <a href="/">PioneerPilot.com</a> will bring you the most up-to-date, most complete, data-driven analysis of the Pioneer metagame on the web. We collect data from online and paper tournaments, compile it into useful statistics, and summarize it into an easy-to-read tier list. Every month we&rsquo;ll update this page to keep you informed with the freshest in-depth data!
        </p>
        <h3>Tier 0</h3>
        <p>
          Tier 0 decks are the absolute best decks in the format, by a wide margin. If you&rsquo;re not playing a Tier 0 deck, you&rsquo;re either attacking the Tier 0 decks directly, or you&rsquo;re at a severe competitive disadvantage. Usually, you&rsquo;re better off <em>playing</em> a Tier 0 deck than trying to beat it. The existence of a Tier 0 deck is rare, and usually results in a ban from Wizards.
        </p>
